cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a method that combines reinforcement learning and optimization for behavior generation in traffic scenarios. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it uses policy-based reinforcement learning. It also involves optimization (cs.RO) to refine the learned behavior. The method is applied to autonomous driving, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses lane-change scenarios, which can involve computer vision (cs.CV) for perception.
